data.content:
In .NET 10 (starting with .NET 9 SR10+), `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was deprecated on Android because the underlying `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` flag was removed by Google.

The recommended replacement is to use **`KeyboardAutoManagerScroll`** or handle insets manually:

## Option 1 – KeyboardAutoManagerScroll (simplest)

.NET MAUI 9+ includes automatic keyboard-aware scrolling. Ensure it's **not** disabled:

```csharp
// In MauiProgram.cs – this is ON by default, just don't disable it
builder.UseMauiApp<App>();
```

If you previously disabled it, remove this line:

```csharp
// REMOVE this if present:
KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect();
```

Then wrap your chat page content in a `ScrollView` or use a `Grid` layout where the `Entry`/`Editor` is in the last row — the framework will scroll it into view automatically.

## Option 2 – Edge-to-edge insets (more control)

In .NET 10, Android uses edge-to-edge mode. You can react to keyboard (IME) insets:

```xml
<!-- Your page layout -->
<Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ... />
    <Entry Grid.Row="1" x:Name="MessageInput" />
</Grid>
```

In your platform-specific Android code or a handler:

```csharp
#if ANDROID
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;

// In your page or custom handler:
ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
    Platform.CurrentActivity.Window.DecorView, 
    new InsetsListener());

class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        // imeInsets.Bottom = keyboard height in px
        // Apply as padding/margin to your root layout
        v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, imeInsets.Bottom);
        return insets;
    }
}
#endif
```

## TL;DR

| Approach | When to use |
|----------|------------|
| `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (default) | Works for most cases — just don't disable it |
| WindowInsets listener | Need precise control over layout when keyboard appears |

Start with Option 1 — if your `Entry` is inside a `ScrollView` or a simple `Grid`, MAUI should handle it automatically in .NET 10.
